article.headline: Bucknell 66, Binghamton 38
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Mike Muscala scored 16 points and had eight rebounds to lead Bucknell to a 66-38 victory over Binghamton on Wednesday night. Bryson Johnson added 10 points for the Bisons (1-2), who opened the season with losses to Big East teams Villanova and Marquette. Twelve players saw action for Bucknell. Bucknell opened the second half on a 10-0 run, expanding its lead to 35-18. Johnson converted a four-point play to start the streak, which was capped by Joe Willman's jumper with 16:35 left in the game. The Bisons went on another 10-0 run later in the second half to extend their advantage to 48-31 with 8:57 remaining. Greer Wright hit four 3-pointers and scored 21 points to lead Binghamton (1-1), which shot 24.6 percent from the field (14 of 57) for the game. Mahamoud Jabbi led Binghamton with 10 rebounds. Willman led Bucknell with nine rebounds.
